               <msContents class="#STM">
                  <summary><p>The <title xml:lang="ta">Caraḷipputtakam</title> by <persName xml:lang="ta" role="author">Iṟāmacāmiyappa</persName>, that is, <persName xml:lang="sa" role="author">Rāmasvāmi</persName>. The work, ("the book on the gamut"), is a musical treatise. The intertitles are names of different types of melody. As noted by Vinson (1867), the first lines give a musical score.</p>
<p>Description based on the examination of the original (October 2021).</p>
<p>Dimensions assessed at the time of examination.</p> </summary>
                  
